    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION: INTRODUCTION - THERMOSTAT OPERATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>THERMOSTAT OPERATION</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef160in07">i.7</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            .
        </para>
        <para>When the engine coolant temperature is below specified thermostat opening temperature, the coolant flows
            through the bypass passage to the water pump because the radiator outlet port is blocked. As the engine
            reaches operating temperature, the thermostat opens, directing coolant towards the radiator; this also
            restricts the bypass opening.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef160in07" figsize="col-wide">
